Current state of P5
<p><a name="id2283987"></a>This is a working document for the use of the TEI Council and
Editors. It summarizes briefly the current state of play and intended
future work with respect to each chapter of P5. For more detailed
information, consult the working directory currently maintained in the
CVS Repository at <tt>tei.sf.net</tt>; for strategic information about the overall goals of the
P5 revision, and the version of it currently visible to the public, see <a class="link_xptr" href="http://www.tei-c.org/P5" target="_top"><span>http://www.tei-c.org/P5</span></a>. </p>
<p><a name="id2284009"></a>This document lists the chapters of P5, with an indication of the current status of each</p>
<p>Under the heading ‘prognosis’, we give our current assessment of the amount
of work needed on each chapter, defined in the following broad terms:
</p><p><dl><dt><strong>stet</strong></dt><dd>No action needed</dd><dt><strong>major surgery</strong></dt><dd>Complete rewrite needed</dd><dt><strong>minor surgery</strong></dt><dd>Basically sound, but new material
needs to be added</dd><dt><strong>convalescent</strong></dt><dd>New material has been approved by
Council and incorporated but editorial work is incomplete</dd><dt><strong>for checking</strong></dt><dd>No major changes anticipated but not
yet checked for P5 consistency</dd><dt><strong>for deletion</strong></dt><dd>Proposed for removal at P5</dd><dt><strong>discharged</strong></dt><dd>No further work is proposed on this chapter</dd></dl></p><p>
</p>
<p><a name="id2284075"></a>All chapters and all validatable examples have been validated
against the current P5 schemas. This validation procedure is now built
in to the process of building a new release, so it should not need
further attention. </p>

